<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-517-745  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 517 745.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  Oct 15 1990 n612 p18(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Yakitori: spreading the technology wealth. (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Lammers, David.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The director of the Open Software Foundation's (OSF) Japanoperation notes that Japanese computer companies have yet to makea significant technological contribution to the OSF, even thoughthe organization numbers Hitachi Ltd among its core sponsors andhas some 20 Japanese member companies.andP;  The problem extends beyondthe OSF and computing, and the director of the Ministry ofInternational Trade and Industry's (MITI) Machinery andInformation Industries division wants Japanese firms to recognizethat the high standard of living in Japan is due at leastpartially to Western technologies licensed by Japanese companiesand that there is need to balance in-house applications oftechnology with the diffusion of technology.andP;  What is needed isfor more Westerners to go to Japan to learn how to tap intoJapanese organizations for information and technology and forJapanese companies to take a proactive approach to thecontribution of people and technologies to organizations like theOSF.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Technology TransferJapanJapanese CompetitionCritique.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>